HEADWORD: Dicyemata
<hw>Di`cy*e"ma*ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>di-</grk> = <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ an embryo.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of worms parasitic in cephalopods. They
are remarkable for the extreme simplicity of their structure. The embryo
exists in two forms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dicyemid</ent>⟦br⟧
